    <h2>Displaying up to date documents, even in the far outback</h2>
    <p>
      So far all digital documents where downloaded every day before leaving on their route because of the sheer size of these pdf files. The internet reception in rural Australia just isn't great enough that it can allow for these documents to be loaded only when they were needed.
    </p>
    <p>
      Our solution was to convert all pdf's to heavily compressed jpg images, page by page. All these images will be displayed as a small thumbnail and only when clicked on a higher resolution version will be displayed, still a lot smaller than the original pdf files.
    </p>
    <p>
      Heavy caching is in place for recently visited pages and files so load time for those are zero to none.
    </p>

  </section>

